<p>March 6, 2012<br /><strong>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</strong><br />
  Contact: Julie Holmquist  952-838-9000, <a href="mailto:julie.holmquist@PACER.org">julie.holmquist@PACER.org</a></p>
<h2 align="center"><strong>&nbsp;&ldquo;Never Ever&rdquo; music video and PACER&rsquo;s National Bullying Prevention   Center show students they  have the power to make a difference</strong></h2>
<p align="center" style="font-size:1.5em"><em>Innovative bullying prevention music video debuts  March 6</em></p>
<p><strong>MINNEAPOLIS</strong><strong>:</strong> &nbsp;An innovative music video debuts March 6 with  the goal of inspiring students to courageously help kids who are bullied. The  new video&mdash;starring more than 40 Ohio  students&mdash;will become part of a nationwide campaign led by <a href="http://www.pacer.org/bullying" title="http://www.pacer.org/bullying">PACER&rsquo;s  National Bullying Prevention Center</a>.</p>
<p>The video features Keenan West&rsquo;s original song, <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8Hj_-kcX3q8" target="_blank">&ldquo;Never Ever,&rdquo;</a> a  celebration of kids who promote kindness and respect and lend a hand to students  who are bullied. West is an Ohio  artist who focuses on creating music with a positive message. A radio version featuring rapper D Griff,  as well as the video version of the song featuring Ohio students, is available for  sale on iTunes and other digital download sites: Look for the iTunes links at: <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8Hj_-kcX3q8" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8Hj_-kcX3q8</a><br />
  &nbsp; <br />
  Fifty cents from every sale will be donated to <a href="https://mail.pacer.org/owa/redir.aspx?C=9025c50080a84230957131f0c2486788&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fwww.pacer.org%2fbullying" target="_blank">PACER&rsquo;s National Bullying Prevention  Center</a> to help fund the nonprofit&rsquo;s free resources available at  PACER.org/bullying.&nbsp; In addition, the video will be included in PACER&rsquo;s  &ldquo;Find the Courage&rdquo; nationwide school campaign. The campaign debuts this fall and  is designed to educate students on how they can positively influence  bullying situations. <br />
  &nbsp;&nbsp;<br />
  &ldquo;This music video  perfectly illustrates the power kids have to take positive action&nbsp;to  address&nbsp;bullying,&rdquo; says Julie Hertzog,  director of PACER&rsquo;s National   Bullying Prevention   Center. </p>
<p>Whip Smart  Productions of Ohio produced the video and Dawn Bierschwal directed.&nbsp;&ldquo;We  wanted to give the kids standing on the sidelines the courage to make a  difference,&rdquo; says Bierschwal. &ldquo;We were incredibly excited to learn that PACER  had a program with the very same objectives!&rdquo;</p>
<p>West and Bierschwal will premiere the video at Sycamore  Junior High in Montgomery, Ohio  on Tuesday, March 6, at 8:20 a.m.  just before it goes live on  YouTube.&nbsp; Watch &ldquo;The Making of  Never Ever&rdquo; at <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0kmTFMxvmvk" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0kmTFMxvmvk</a></p>
PACER&rsquo;s National   Bullying Prevention   Center provides  interactive resources designed to benefit all students. It offers educators, students, families and individuals  the tools they need to address bullying in schools, recreational programs or  community organizations. For more information, visit PACER.org/bullying  or call 952-838-9000.
